Merge pull request #224 from mainej/master modernize vim recipe; remove rvm dependency

Simplify vim install; remove RVM dependency This commit does a number of things to simplify and improve the vim
recipe:

- Re-enable Command-T.

- Remove dependency on RVM.  Both MacVim, and Command-T must be compiled
  with the system ruby.  Originally we used RVM to access the system
  ruby, but not everyone wants to use RVM.  The latest versions of
  homebrew use the system ruby automatically when installing MacVim, so
  that part is already fixed.  This commit compiles Command-T with the
  system ruby too, using similar tactics to homebrew.

- MacVim also installs a command line vim.  Use that one everywhere,
  instead of installing a separate command line vim.  This does NOT mean
  you have to use MacVim or that the command line doesn't work, only
  that they both rely on the same underlying install of vim.

- Remove dependency on mercurial, because we don't need to download vim
  from a mercurial repo.

- Stop blowing away ~/.vim on every run of soloist.  This was causing
  soloist to re-download every vim plugin on every run.  If you really
  want to force soloist to re-install vim, do something like the
  following:
    brew uninstall macvim
    rm -rf ~/.vim*
    rm -rf /Applications/MacVim.app

This commit builds on Doc Ritezel's initial work to modernize the vim
recipe.

Switch to Bash-It ## Additions
* LWRP for bash-it aliases, completion, plugins
* LWRP for custom plugin installation

## Removals
* The `bash_profile_include` LWRP
* `arch_flags` for Snow Leopard
* `lang_en`
* `ree_settings`
* recipe `gem_no_rdoc_no_ri` (replaced by `gem_setup`)

## Ported to Bash-It
* `better_history`
* `ctrl-o`
* `ctrl-s`
* `no_sudo_gem_install` (called by `gem_setup` now)
* `ec2_api_tools`

## Reimplemented by Bash-It
* bash path order
* PS1 management
* aliases
* git completion
* rbenv integration
* `rvm`

postgres:  PATH requires /usr/local/bin > /usr/bin proper postgres installation requires /usr/local/bin to appear before
/usr/bin.  The reason is that Apple's version of postgres keeps its
executables in /usr/bin, whereas homebrew's version of postgres keeps it
in /usr/local/bin.  We want, of course, to use the homebrew version
first.

Make vim recipe work from scratch The recipe had many problems.

1. MacVim must be compiled with system ruby.
2. The not_if blocks were written as if they were run between
commands, when in reality they are all run before any command.
This meant that they could only have worked on a subsequent
run.  Removed many of the not_if blocks... give chef control
of vi.  Or don't use chef.
3. The casecommons/vim-config git repo isn't available publicly.
Using pivotal/vim-config instead.
4. The multiple commands to download the vim-config repo were
breaking submodule init.
5. command-t must be compiled with system ruby.
